            Summary = "Complete reference for every field, button, status, validation rule, tab, table column, and action in the Customers module.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.QuickRef,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 3,
            AppRoutes = """["/customers"]""",
            Tags = """["customers","reference"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"title":"Customers Field Reference","groups":[{"heading":"Customer Create/Edit Form Fields","items":[{"label":"Name (required)","value":"The customer's display name. Can't be blank. Up to 200 characters."},{"label":"Company Name","value":"The customer's business name. Optional. Shows under the name in the detail header."},{"label":"Email","value":"Optional. Must be a valid email. Up to 200 characters. Shows as a clickable email link in the header."},{"label":"Phone","value":"Optional. Formats as (XXX) XXX-XXXX. Shows as a clickable phone link in the header."},{"label":"Active (edit only)","value":"An on/off switch, shown only when you edit an existing customer. Controls whether they show up in active-only views. New customers start active."}]},{"heading":"Customer List Table Columns","items":[{"label":"Name","value":"Sortable. The customer's display name."},{"label":"Company","value":"Sortable. Company name, or a dash if none."},{"label":"Email","value":"Sortable. Email, or a dash if none."},{"label":"Phone","value":"Sortable. Phone, or a dash if none."},{"label":"Active","value":"Sortable and filterable. A green Active label or a gray Inactive label."},{"label":"Contacts","value":"Sortable. How many contacts this customer has."},{"label":"Jobs","value":"Sortable. How many jobs this customer has."},{"label":"Created","value":"Sortable. When the customer was created (MM/dd/yyyy)."}]},{"heading":"Stats Bar Metrics","items":[{"label":"Open Estimates","value":"How many estimates are still open. Click to jump to the Estimates tab."},{"label":"Open Quotes","value":"How many quotes are active. Click to jump to the Quotes tab."},{"label":"Open Orders","value":"How many sales orders are in progress. Click to jump to the Orders tab."},{"label":"Active Jobs","value":"How many jobs are currently active. Click to jump to the Jobs tab."},{"label":"Outstanding","value":"Total dollar amount of unpaid invoices. Click to jump to the Invoices tab."},{"label":"YTD Revenue","value":"Total revenue from this customer so far this year. Not clickable."}]},{"heading":"Detail Page Tabs","items":[{"label":"Overview","value":"Account details, accounting info when connected, and the Credit Status card."},{"label":"Contacts","value":"Contact cards with initials, name, role, email, phone, and a Primary badge. Add, edit, and remove."},{"label":"Interactions","value":"A log of calls, emails, meetings, and notes. Filter by contact and type. Add, edit, and delete."},{"label":"Addresses","value":"Address cards with a type label (Billing, Shipping, and so on), a Default badge, and full address lines. View only."},{"label":"Estimates","value":"Rough ballpark figures. Shows title, amount, status, valid-until, and created date. Create, edit, delete, and convert to a quote."},{"label":"Quotes","value":"Firm, line-by-line quotes. Shows quote number, status, total, expiration, and created date. Click to open a quote."},{"label":"Orders","value":"Sales orders. Shows order number, status, total, requested date, and created date. Click to open an order."},{"label":"Jobs","value":"Linked jobs. Shows title, stage, due date, and created date. Click to open a job."},{"label":"Invoices","value":"Invoices sent. Shows invoice number, status, total, due date, and created date. Click to open an invoice."},{"label":"Activity","value":"A time-ordered history of every change, comment, and event."}]},{"heading":"Contact Form Fields","items":[{"label":"First Name (required)","value":"Up to 100 characters. Shown as Last, First across the app."},{"label":"Last Name (required)","value":"Up to 100 characters."},{"label":"Email","value":"Optional. Must be a valid email. Up to 200 characters. Shows as a clickable email link on the card."},{"label":"Phone","value":"Optional. Formats as (XXX) XXX-XXXX. Shows as a clickable phone link on the card."},{"label":"Role","value":"Optional. Pick from a menu of roles set up for your shop. '-- None --' leaves it blank."},{"label":"Primary Contact","value":"An on/off switch. When on, marks this person as the main contact, shown with a blue Primary badge on the card."}]},{"heading":"Interaction Form Fields","items":[{"label":"Type (required)","value":"Pick from a menu: Call, Email, Meeting, or Note. Each type shows its own icon in the table."},{"label":"Contact","value":"Optional. Ties the entry to a specific contact. The menu lists this customer's contacts plus '-- All Contacts --'."},{"label":"Subject (required)","value":"Up to 200 characters. A short description of what happened."},{"label":"Date (required)","value":"Pick the date it happened. Defaults to today."},{"label":"Duration (minutes)","value":"Optional. How long it lasted, in minutes."},{"label":"Notes","value":"Optional. Room for detailed notes about the interaction."}]},{"heading":"Interaction Table Columns","items":[{"label":"Type","value":"Sortable and filterable. A labeled icon for Call, Email, Meeting, or Note."},{"label":"Subject","value":"Sortable. The interaction's subject."},{"label":"Contact","value":"Sortable. Contact name (Last, First)."},{"label":"Logged By","value":"Sortable. Who recorded the interaction."},{"label":"Date","value":"Sortable. When it happened (MM/dd/yyyy)."},{"label":"Duration","value":"Sortable. How long it lasted, in minutes."},{"label":"Actions","value":"Edit and delete buttons."}]},{"heading":"Estimate Form Fields","items":[{"label":"Title (required)","value":"Up to 300 characters. A short title for the estimate."},{"label":"Description","value":"Optional. A fuller description of what the estimate covers."},{"label":"Estimated Amount (required)","value":"A dollar amount. Must be zero or more."},{"label":"Valid Until","value":"Optional. When the estimate expires."},{"label":"Status (edit only)","value":"Shown only when editing. Choose Draft, Sent, Accepted, Declined, or Expired."},{"label":"Notes","value":"Optional. Internal notes."}]},{"heading":"Estimate Table Columns","items":[{"label":"Title","value":"Sortable. The estimate title."},{"label":"Amount","value":"Sortable. The estimated amount, shown as currency."},{"label":"Status","value":"Sortable and filterable. A colored label: Draft, Sent, Accepted, Declined, or Expired."},{"label":"Valid Until","value":"Sortable. When the estimate expires (MM/dd/yyyy)."},{"label":"Created","value":"Sortable. When it was created (MM/dd/yyyy)."},{"label":"Actions","value":"A Convert to Quote button (hidden once converted) and a Delete button."}]},{"heading":"Credit Status Card Fields","items":[{"label":"Risk Level","value":"A label: Low (green), Medium (yellow), High (red), or On Hold (red). Based on how much credit is used and whether there's a hold."},{"label":"Credit Hold Banner","value":"A red banner shown when the customer is on hold. Displays the reason and a Release button."},{"label":"Credit Limit","value":"A dollar amount, or 'None' if no limit is set. The most credit this customer can carry."},{"label":"Open Balance","value":"The total of unpaid invoices."},{"label":"Pending Orders","value":"The total of in-progress sales orders not yet invoiced."},{"label":"Total Exposure","value":"Open balance plus pending orders. Turns red when over the limit."},{"label":"Available Credit","value":"The credit limit minus total exposure. Turns red when negative. Shown only when a limit is set."},{"label":"Utilization","value":"How much of the credit limit is used, as a percentage. Shown only when a limit is set."},{"label":"Utilization Bar","value":"A bar showing credit used. Turns red when it goes over 100%."},{"label":"Place Hold Button","value":"Opens a window to put the customer on credit hold with a required reason (up to 500 characters). Blocks new orders."},{"label":"Release Button","value":"Shown on the hold banner. Removes the hold and lets new orders through again."}]},{"heading":"Address Card Fields","items":[{"label":"Type","value":"A label showing the address type: Billing, Shipping, or another type you've set up."},{"label":"Default","value":"A blue Default badge on the default address."},{"label":"Line 1","value":"The main street address line."},{"label":"Line 2","value":"A second address line (suite, unit, and so on). Shown only when set."},{"label":"City, State ZIP","value":"City, two-letter state code, and ZIP on one line."},{"label":"Country","value":"The country name."}]},{"heading":"Quotes Tab Table Columns","items":[{"label":"Quote #","value":"Sortable. The quote's reference number."},{"label":"Status","value":"Sortable and filterable. A colored label: Draft, Sent, Accepted, Declined, or Expired."},{"label":"Total","value":"Sortable. The quote total, shown as currency."},{"label":"Expiration Date","value":"Sortable. When the quote expires (MM/dd/yyyy)."},{"label":"Created","value":"Sortable. When it was created (MM/dd/yyyy)."}]},{"heading":"Orders Tab Table Columns","items":[{"label":"Order #","value":"Sortable. The sales order's reference number."},{"label":"Status","value":"Sortable and filterable. A colored status label."},{"label":"Total","value":"Sortable. The order total, shown as currency."},{"label":"Requested Date","value":"Sortable. The customer's requested delivery date (MM/dd/yyyy)."},{"label":"Created","value":"Sortable. When the order was created (MM/dd/yyyy)."}]},{"heading":"Jobs Tab Table Columns","items":[{"label":"Title","value":"Sortable. The job title."},{"label":"Stage","value":"Sortable. A colored label matching the job's stage on the board."},{"label":"Due Date","value":"Sortable. The job's due date (MM/dd/yyyy)."},{"label":"Created","value":"Sortable. When the job was created (MM/dd/yyyy)."}]},{"heading":"Invoices Tab Table Columns","items":[{"label":"Invoice #","value":"Sortable. The invoice's reference number."},{"label":"Status","value":"Sortable and filterable. A colored status label."},{"label":"Total","value":"Sortable. The invoice total, shown as currency."},{"label":"Due Date","value":"Sortable. When payment is due (MM/dd/yyyy)."},{"label":"Created","value":"Sortable. When the invoice was created (MM/dd/yyyy)."}]},{"heading":"Buttons and Actions","items":[{"label":"Add Customer (list page)","value":"Opens the quick form with Name, Company, Email, and Phone."},{"label":"Save (create form)","value":"Creates the customer. Grayed out until the form is valid or while it's saving. Hover to see what still needs attention. Takes you to the new customer's page."},{"label":"Edit (detail page)","value":"Turns the header into edit mode right on the page (no separate window). The Overview identity fields become editable, with Save and Cancel inline. Includes the Active switch, which isn't in the create form."},{"label":"Archive (detail page)","value":"An archive button. Asks you to confirm, then archives the customer and returns you to the list. Nothing is truly deleted."},{"label":"Back to Customers","value":"A link in the detail header that returns you to the customer list."},{"label":"Add Contact","value":"On the Contacts tab. Opens the new-contact form."},{"label":"Edit Contact","value":"The edit button on each contact card. Opens the contact's details to change them."},{"label":"Remove Contact","value":"The delete button on each contact card. Asks you to confirm first."},{"label":"Log Interaction","value":"On the Interactions tab. Opens the new-interaction form."},{"label":"Edit Interaction","value":"The edit button on an interaction row. Opens it to change the details."},{"label":"Delete Interaction","value":"The delete button on an interaction row. Asks you to confirm first."},{"label":"New Estimate","value":"On the Estimates tab. Opens the new-estimate form."},{"label":"Convert to Quote (estimate)","value":"The convert button on an estimate row. Turns the estimate into a formal quote. Hidden once it's been converted."},{"label":"Delete Estimate","value":"The delete button on an estimate row. Asks you to confirm first."},{"label":"Place Hold","value":"A button on the Credit Status card. Opens a window to enter a hold reason."},{"label":"Release Hold","value":"A button on the credit-hold banner. Lifts the hold right away."}]},{"heading":"Validation Rules","items":[{"label":"Customer Name","value":"Required. Up to 200 characters. Can't be blank."},{"label":"Customer Email","value":"Optional. Must be a valid email when provided. Up to 200 characters."},{"label":"Contact First Name","value":"Required. Up to 100 characters."},{"label":"Contact Last Name","value":"Required. Up to 100 characters."},{"label":"Contact Email","value":"Optional. Must be a valid email. Up to 200 characters."},{"label":"Interaction Type","value":"Required. Must be Call, Email, Meeting, or Note."},{"label":"Interaction Subject","value":"Required. Up to 200 characters."},{"label":"Interaction Date","value":"Required. Must pick a date."},{"label":"Estimate Title","value":"Required. Up to 300 characters."},{"label":"Estimated Amount","value":"Required. Must be zero or more."},{"label":"Credit Hold Reason","value":"Required when placing a hold. Up to 500 characters."},{"label":"Save button hint","value":"When the form isn't complete, hovering over Save lists which fields still need attention."}]}]}"""
        });

        // ── Knowledge Check (Quiz) ───────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Customers Knowledge Check",
            Slug = "customers-quiz",
            Summary = "Test your knowledge of the Customers module: detail tabs, contacts, credit management, estimates, interactions, and the quote-to-cash flow.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Quiz,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 4,
            AppRoutes = """["/customers"]""",
            Tags = """["customers","quiz"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"passingScore":80,"questionsPerQuiz":8,"shuffleOptions":true,"showExplanationsAfterSubmit":true,"questions":[{"id":"cu1","text":"A new customer calls to request a quote. What's the first step in Forge?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Create a quote directly from the Quotes page"},{"id":"b","text":"Go to Customers, click Add Customer, fill in their details, then create an estimate or quote from their detail page","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Create a job on the board and assign the customer later"},{"id":"d","text":"Add them to the Leads module and wait for conversion"}],"explanation":"Start by creating the customer record. From their detail page you can create estimates or quotes right in the Estimates or Quotes tabs, which keeps all their activity linked to them."},{"id":"cu2","text":"You're on a customer's detail page and want to quickly see how many active jobs they have. Where do you look?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Open the Jobs tab and count the rows"},{"id":"b","text":"Check the stats bar — the Active Jobs number shows the count, and clicking it jumps to the Jobs tab","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Run a report filtered by customer name"},{"id":"d","text":"Go to the board and filter by customer"}],"explanation":"The stats bar under the customer header shows live totals, including Active Jobs. Each stat is clickable — clicking Active Jobs jumps straight to the Jobs tab."},{"id":"cu3","text":"A customer's credit status shows Total Exposure in red. What does that mean?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The customer has been on hold for more than 30 days"},{"id":"b","text":"What they owe plus their pending orders is over their credit limit","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The customer has invoices more than 90 days overdue"},{"id":"d","text":"The customer's account has been flagged for review"}],"explanation":"Total exposure is the open balance owed plus pending orders. When that goes over the credit limit, it shows in red to warn you the customer is past their allowed credit."},{"id":"cu4","text":"You need to block a customer from placing new orders because of unpaid invoices. How?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Set the customer to inactive in edit mode"},{"id":"b","text":"Delete all their open sales orders"},{"id":"c","text":"On the Overview tab, click Place Hold on the Credit Status card and enter a reason","isCorrect":true},{"id":"d","text":"Ask your admin to disable their account"}],"explanation":"The Credit Status card on the Overview tab has a Place Hold button. Click it, enter a reason, and new orders are blocked until you release the hold."},{"id":"cu5","text":"A customer contact was promoted and their role changed. Where do you update it?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Go to Admin and update their role there"},{"id":"b","text":"Open the customer's Contacts tab, click the edit button on their card, and change the Role","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Edit the contact from the customer list page"},{"id":"d","text":"The role can't be changed after the contact is created"}],"explanation":"On the Contacts tab, each card has an edit button. Click it to open the contact and change any field, including the Role. Role choices come from your shop's setup."},{"id":"cu6","text":"You just had a phone call with a customer about an upcoming project. Where do you log it?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Add a note on the Activity tab"},{"id":"b","text":"Create a new estimate on the Estimates tab"},{"id":"c","text":"Go to the Interactions tab, click Log Interaction, choose Call, and fill in the subject, date, duration, and notes","isCorrect":true},{"id":"d","text":"Send an email from the Contacts tab"}],"explanation":"The Interactions tab is where you track customer communications. Click Log Interaction, choose Call, and fill in the details, including any notes from the conversation."},{"id":"cu7","text":"A customer has accepted an estimate. What's the next step in the quote-to-cash flow?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Create a job straight from the estimate"},{"id":"b","text":"Click Convert to Quote on the estimate row to create a firm, line-by-line quote","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Change the estimate's status to Converted by hand"},{"id":"d","text":"Delete the estimate and create a sales order instead"}],"explanation":"Estimates are rough ballpark figures. Once accepted, use Convert to Quote to create a firm, line-by-line quote, which can then become a sales order. The convert button is hidden once the estimate is converted."},{"id":"cu8","text":"How is a customer's set of detail tabs decided, and which tab has the Credit Status card?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"There are always exactly 10 fixed tabs, and the Credit Status card is on the Invoices tab"},{"id":"b","text":"The tabs adapt to where the customer is (Active, Prospect, or Archived), and the Credit Status card is on the Overview tab","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"There's a fixed Credit tab that always appears and holds the Credit Status card"},{"id":"d","text":"The tabs are the same for every customer, and the Credit Status card is on a Financials tab"}],"explanation":"The tabs aren't fixed — they change based on where the customer is. Overview is always first and Activity always last. Active customers also see Contacts, Addresses, Estimates, Quotes, Orders, Jobs, Invoices, Pricing, and Interactions (11 in all); Prospects see a shorter set (7); Archived customers see a read-only history set (6). The Credit Status card always lives on the Overview tab."},{"id":"cu9","text":"You want to find all inactive customers created in the last year. How do you filter the list?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Set the filter to Inactive, then sort by the Created column to find the recent ones","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Search for 'inactive' in the search box"},{"id":"c","text":"Go to Reports and build a custom customer report"},{"id":"d","text":"You can't filter inactive customers — they're hidden by default"}],"explanation":"The customer list has an Active/Inactive filter. Set it to Inactive to show only inactive customers, then sort by the Created column to find the most recent ones."},{"id":"cu10","text":"What shows on a contact card in the Contacts tab?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Just the contact's name and email"},{"id":"b","text":"Their initials, name (Last, First), role, email link, phone link, and a Primary badge when it applies","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Name, job title, department, and office location"},{"id":"d","text":"Name, email, and a list of their recent interactions"}],"explanation":"Contact cards show the person's initials, their name as Last, First, their role, clickable email and phone links, and a blue Primary badge if they're the main contact."},{"id":"cu11","text":"A customer's credit usage bar is red at 115%. What can you do?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Nothing — the system blocks orders automatically when over the limit"},{"id":"b","text":"Place a credit hold, raise the credit limit through your accounting system, or collect on unpaid invoices to lower the balance","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Delete the oldest unpaid invoices to bring the balance down"},{"id":"d","text":"Archive the customer to stop further orders"}],"explanation":"When a customer is over their limit, you can place a credit hold to block new orders (with a reason), work with accounting to raise the limit, or collect on unpaid invoices to lower the balance owed and bring usage back under 100%."},{"id":"cu12","text":"You want to share a direct link to a customer's Orders tab with a coworker. How do you get that link?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"You can't link to one tab — a shared link only ever opens the customer list"},{"id":"b","text":"Open the customer, click the Orders tab, then copy the page link from your browser — it updates to point right at that tab","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"You have to tell your coworker in words which tab to open; there is no shareable link"},{"id":"d","text":"Type the customer's name into the search box and send that text instead"}],"explanation":"When you open a customer and switch to a tab, the page link updates to point at that customer on that tab. Copy it from your browser to bookmark or share it — opening it later reopens that customer with the Orders tab already selected."},{"id":"cu13","text":"What's the difference between an estimate and a quote on a customer?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"They're the same thing with different names"},{"id":"b","text":"Estimates are rough ballpark figures with a single amount; quotes are firm, line-by-line commitments with a price for each item","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Estimates are for new customers; quotes are for existing ones"},{"id":"d","text":"Estimates need approval; quotes don't"}],"explanation":"Estimates are rough ballpark figures with a single amount — quick and informal. Quotes are firm commitments with a line for each item (part, quantity, unit price). You can convert an estimate to a quote when the customer is ready for a firm price."},{"id":"cu14","text":"On the Interactions tab, you want to see only meetings with one specific contact. How?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Type 'meeting' in the search box"},{"id":"b","text":"Set the Contact filter to that person and the Type filter to Meeting","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Sort by the Type column and scroll to the meeting rows"},{"id":"d","text":"You can't filter by both contact and type at the same time"}],"explanation":"The Interactions tab has two filters: Contact (a specific person or '-- All Contacts --') and Type (Call, Email, Meeting, Note, or '-- All Types --'). You can use both at once."},{"id":"cu15","text":"When you archive a customer, what happens to their data?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Everything is permanently deleted, including contacts, orders, and invoices"},{"id":"b","text":"The customer is set aside — all their history is kept, but they no longer show in active views","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Only the customer name is kept; all related records are removed"},{"id":"d","text":"The customer is moved to a separate archive database"}],"explanation":"Archiving keeps everything — contacts, orders, jobs, invoices, and activity history are all preserved. The customer simply stops showing in the standard views. Forge never truly deletes records."}]}"""
        });

        // ── Creating Customers (Article) ─────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Creating Customers",
            Slug = "customers-creating",
            Summary = "The three ways to create a customer — Quick add, Convert from Lead, and Guided setup — and how to walk through the guided customer wizard at /customers/new.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 6,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 5,
            AppRoutes = """["/customers","/customers/new"]""",
            Tags = """["customers","create","onboarding","wizard"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Creating Customers\n\nClicking **+ New Customer** on the Customers list doesn't jump straight into a form. Instead it opens a small window that asks *how* you want to create the customer. There are three paths, and picking the right one saves time.\n\n### The Three Ways to Create\n\nWhen you click **+ New Customer**, that window offers three choices:\n\n1. **Quick add** (the highlighted, recommended choice, marked 'Fastest'). Opens a single form: Name, Company, Email, Phone, plus optional Credit Limit, Default Currency, and billing/shipping addresses. Best when you just need the record in the system *now* and will fill in the rest later. Only **Name** is required.\n2. **Convert from lead**. Opens a lead picker — search your existing leads, click one, and the system creates the customer in one step, links the original lead, and carries its contacts and outreach preferences over for you. Use this whenever a lead already exists so you don't retype company and contact details.\n3. **Guided setup**. Walks you through a step-by-step wizard. Best for an important new customer worth a thorough setup — credit terms, tax exemption, and addresses captured up front.\n\nClick **Cancel** to back out without creating anything.\n\n### Path 1 — Quick Add\n\nThe quick form is a single screen. Enter the **Name** (required), and optionally Company, Email, Phone, Credit Limit, Default Currency, and a billing and/or shipping address. The **Save** button stays grayed out until the form is valid; the warning icon next to it lists anything that still needs attention. After you save, you land on the new customer's detail page.\n\nNew customers start out **Active**, so a brand-new record with no open business shows the **Prospect** set of tabs until business starts coming in.\n\n### Path 2 — Convert from Lead\n\nChoosing **Convert from lead** opens the lead picker. Type in the search box to filter by company or contact, then click the lead you want. Conversion is a **single step** — the system creates the customer and takes you to their new page. Add the credit limit, tax details, and addresses afterward on the detail page using the normal edit steps.\n\n### Path 3 — Guided Setup\n\nThe guided wizard walks you through four steps (the same step-by-step layout used for Parts and Vendors):\n\n1. **Identity** (required) — Name (required), Company, Email, Phone. Saving this step creates the customer record.\n2. **Addresses** (optional) — capture billing and shipping addresses up front.\n3. **Credit & Tax** (optional) — Credit Limit, Default Currency, and a Tax Exempt switch. Turning on **Tax Exempt** adds a required **Tax Exemption ID** field.\n4. **Review** (required) — a read-only summary of everything you entered. Confirm to finish.\n\nThe wizard also has an **Express** switch that collapses the steps into one screen if you'd rather fill everything at once. Each step saves as you go, and your progress is saved in the web address, so you can refresh or share the in-progress link without losing your work.\n\n### Which Path Should I Use?\n\n- **Just need the record fast?** Quick add.\n- **A lead already exists?** Convert from lead — never retype what you already captured.\n- **An important new account you want set up properly?** Guided setup.\n\nAll three paths end in the same place: the customer's detail page, where the adaptive tabs take over.","sections":[]}"""
        });

        // ── Creating Customers (Walkthrough) ─────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
